they love me! they REALLY love me!!!

after roughly twenty-four years of hearing loss, this mama is getting it back, bionic style!!

in about a month or so i will have a procedure to have a bone anchored hearing aid implanted! this procedure is an outpatient procedure which involves my dr inserting a surgical screw into the bone behind my ear and placing a little device (almost like a bluetooth) on top! 

my dr and several other professionals (a whole panel to be exact) went over my case and determined that i am the perfect candidate for this due to the type of hearing loss i have. during tests, it was discovered that i have greatest hearing results through bone conductivity (vibrations) vs what other traditional hearing aids do, which is amplify noise

it goes without saying that while iâ€™m pretty excited for this, i am also nervous as all get out!
